%N A349948 Tetrahedral-sided isosceles Heron triangle pairs.
%C A349948 Isosceles Heron triangle pairs with tetrahedral sides: [t(a(n)+1), t(a(n)+1), t(a(n))] and [t(a(n)+6), t(a(n)+5), t(a(n)+5)] where t(n) = A000292(n) is a tetrahedral number, i.e., t(n) = n*(n+1)*(n+2)/6. The Heron triangle pair areas have been checked for rationality to 100 terms of {a(n)}.
%C A349948 Not all isosceles Heron triangles with tetrahedral sides are generated by this sequence. For example, [t(63),t(50),t(50)] is not included. Also, scalene Heron triangles with tetrahedral sides are not included. For example, [t(111),t(104),t(62)]. - _Michael Somos_, Mar 27 2022
%C A349948 Area of triangles: T1(n) = (b(n)-2)^2*(b(n)-3)^2*(b(n)-4)*c(n)/48 and T2(n) = (b(n)+2)^2*(b(n)+3)^2*(b(n)+4)*c(n)/48, where b(n) = A003500(n) and c(n) =  A052530(n). - _Randall L Rathbun_, Apr 01 2022
%C A349948 Conjecture: for k a positive integer, the sequence {a(k^n): n >= 1} is a strong divisibility sequence; that is, for n, m >= 1,  gcd(a(k^n), a(k^m)) = a(k^gcd(n,m)). - _Peter Bala_, Dec 03 2022
